{"TopicId":191270,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"Bulb Evolved","CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T20:17:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T20:17:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(211,84,0);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003ECurrent Version : 1.8.x\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(192,57,43);\u0022\u003EDownload : \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(192,57,43);\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/2316/Bulb%20Evolved\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESpaceDoc\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Jiraiyah/Module-Light-Bulb/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGitHub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:24px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(192,57,43);\u0022\u003ESource : \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Jiraiyah/Module-Light-Bulb\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EGitHub\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe are all familiar with the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/149686-13-alshains-modlets-electric-lights-localizer-helper-advanced-tweakables-button-bulb/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EORIGINAL\u003C/a\u003E bulb plugin, the main developer didn\u0027t update the mod for long time and different people are maintaining it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere are some issues with the original code, the developer was using complex code to handle color change on light, and emissive color for the material.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow ever, it had issues with the editor, in other words, the emissive color wouldn\u0027t show up in some cases. Also, he would only change one light and one emissive color.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe code is rewritten using a template from very old plugin (Module Surface Light). The way this plugin is handling the events was much more flexible and made the code lots smaller and easier. So, I took it on myself, to rewrite the bulb code using this template, at the same time, fixing the issues with emissive color change and made it so that no matter how many lights and emissive objects we have, it will behave properly on all of them. Also, added two attributes to the module, these two are multipliers for the emissive color, they work hand in hand in the math formula, so with playing with the numbers, combined with the colors, you can achieve very nice effects on your light objects.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe License for original Bulb is\u00A0GPLv3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe License for \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139724-18-surface-mounted-lights-v114-incompatible-with-ksp-17/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EModule Surface Light\u003C/a\u003E is\u00A0\u003Cem style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(53,60,65);font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECreative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-01-31T03:57:47Z\u0022 title=\u002201/31/2020 03:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 31, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Jiraiyah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T20:48:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere should the files be installed? They\u0027re all in the root of the ZIP file. Usually there\u0027s a mod folder in there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JadeOfMaar","CreatedById":167617,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T22:41:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a very nice little thing to have. But as HebaruSan above is asking: Why doesn\u0027t your zip file have a folder structure? This is very much needed in order for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E to know how to organize it in an install, and so players who install manually have an idea where the files go. This is vital to the operation of a mod or anything that\u0027s downloaded and run. Try to always remember and to always meet this requirement when you do a release. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T23:45:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, most mods all go in the same place.\u00A0 I can see \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E having issues, but I would hope we have enough faith in humanity for manual installers to figure it out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: So there\u0027s no folder at all.\u00A0 I see.\u00A0 Well, I\u0027ll concede\u00A0a mod folder at the very least would be worthwhile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-01-29T23:47:58Z\u0022 title=\u002201/29/2020 11:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 29, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by klgraham1013\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-29T23:47:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223733979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580330930\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhere should the files be installed? They\u0027re all in the root of the ZIP file. Usually there\u0027s a mod folder in there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOuch, I screwed Up in the folder zipping, just make a \u0022Module Bulb Light\u0022 folder and put stuff in it, will fix it in few hours\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-30T01:26:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncongrats on the release.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u002B1 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rep:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/rep.png\u0022 title=\u0022:rep:\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223734043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580341652\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297667\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jiraiyah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jiraiyah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOuch, I screwed Up in the folder zipping, just make a \u0022Module Bulb Light\u0022 folder and put stuff in it, will fix it in few hours\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwe\u0027ve all been there. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-30T01:32:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223734070\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580347577\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190933\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022zer0Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, zer0Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223734043\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221580341652\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297667\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jiraiyah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jiraiyah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOuch, I screwed Up in the folder zipping, just make a \u0022Module Bulb Light\u0022 folder and put stuff in it, will fix it in few hours\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwe\u0027ve all been there. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBelieve me, I know it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-01-31T03:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed the issue with folder structure,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- updated spacedoc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Added Git Repository and Release page\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-03T11:12:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsorry for being inactive for so long, life happens, any one can take this over so that I can add him to the spacedoc page as author please? These days I\u0027m really busy and can\u0027t handle updating mods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hildimar","CreatedById":210878,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-11T14:56:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone using this mod in 1.11.2? The lights are lit in orange when starting despite being turned off and also always turning back to orange when turned off and on or blinking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alberro\u002B","CreatedById":199496,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-11T16:05:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes with mods, the little things are what make a huge difference. I had this installed back when I started playing, good to see that it\u0027s still here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-04-11T16:06:11Z\u0022 title=\u002204/11/2021 04:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EApril 11, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by alberro\u002B\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}